I’d like to talk about a time when I helped my best friend through a difficult breakup, which is probably one of the most meaningful things I’ve ever done for her.

This happened about three years ago when I was still in high school. At that time, my best friend, My, had been in a relationship with a boy from another class for over a year. She was deeply in love with him and often talked about him whenever we met.

However, things took a turn for the worse when she discovered that he had been chatting with another girl behind her back. She was completely shocked and heartbroken. She came to me for advice and asked whether she should forgive him, as he had apologized and promised to change.

After thinking about it carefully, I advised her to end the relationship, because I believed that trust is essential in any relationship. If he truly cared about her, he wouldn’t have behaved that way in the first place.

After a few days of consideration, she decided to break up with him. It was an incredibly difficult decision for her, so I did my best to support her emotionally. I regularly checked in on her, spent time with her, and encouraged her to stay positive. Gradually, she was able to move on and feel better.

Looking back, I feel really glad that I was there for her during such a tough time. Seeing her happy again now makes me feel that my support truly made a difference.
